What you need to know:  It is the most controversial World Cup in history, with Qatar dogged ever since it was named host in 2010 by accusations of vote-buying – which were hotly denied – and questions over the country's suitability.From human rights concerns to the ongoing war in Ukraine, it has been impossible to keep the spotlight solely on the sport, but Fifa president Gianni Infantino has repeated, as he did on Thursday, that it "will be a fantastic and unique World Cup".